    "created_at": "2012-01-24T07:37:44Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-01-24T07:37:44Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Implementation wise I think you did a great job, it looks clean and slick.  However...\n\nI hate to say this, but I personally don't like it _at all_, because it has a non-trivial cost in vertical space.  I measured and on my laptop, I can fit 9 1/2 one-line cells with one-line output using current master, and with this applied I can only fit 8 1/2, so there's a ~10% loss of usable vertical space.  Given that 10 cells total is already very little to begin with, losing anything at this point really hurts, big time.\n\nFurthermore, creating a new cell with the mouse isn't all that useful to me, since I'll immediately need to go back to the keyboard to type again, so it's a fairly flow-disrupting action.\n\nNow, I also realize that this is most likely to benefit less experienced/advanced users, who may prefer a mouse action to remembering a keybinding or using a menu option...\n\nBut the benefit to new users would need to be really huge to justify the loss of extremely valuable real estate forever.  It's kind of like soldering the training wheels onto the bike, so you can never get rid of them even once you know how to ride, and you're stuck with this annoyance forever.\n\nSorry to take this view, but huge -1 on this one from me.  If there's overwhelming user demand for this feature, I'm willing to discuss it, obviously...\n"
  },
