    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Another option is to add a small context menu to the right of each cell to insert new cell below or delete that cell.  Instead of taking up vertical space, this could just take up the last couple of characters of width of the cell.\n\nPersonally, I think it would be better to add this or the triangle above on the right side, so it's not visually cluttering up the start of the lines of code.\n\nOne problem that we have in Sage is that the \"blue bar\" (small div between cells to add a new cell) is not very easy to discover or target, and it's not obvious that shift-click adds a text cell.  We've played with the idea of adding explicit \"code\" and \"text\" links to the div.  I'm interested in seeing what you guys come up with for a UI.\n"
  },
