    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@fperez:  I am actually glad you bring up these points.  Most people don't use the keyboard as much as you do, and for those users this is a huge improvement.  BUT, I don't like the fact that this makes the UI have a flashy feel, meaning that things flash on/off as you move around.  Our current api is so clean and simple and I am very hesitant to clutter it up in this way.  I also agree that the vertical space is an issue that we don't want to compromise on.  Some options:\n- We just abandon this idea.\n- We try to go with @Carreau s idea of making a less flash, less vertical space sucking icon on the L.\n- We could also provide an option in the view menu to collapse this space for advanced users wanting the simpler UI and more vertical space.\n"
