    "created_at": "2012-01-25T00:06:05Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-01-25T00:06:05Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "If making it optional is not too complex, I'd be OK with that.  I'm happy if advanced users need to tweak a few things for their use patterns, and I think the out-of-the-box experience should favor the new users.  What I don't like are things that are impossible to change once a user advances in his/her use patterns to more advanced ones and doesn't need the 'training wheels' anymore.\n\nI'm not crazy about the little triangle icon @Carreau suggested only b/c it seems really small, and super-small targets are harder to hit.  Your original solution had the advantage of being huge in one dimension, and hence required much less hand-eye fine coordination to hit: you only had to be somewhat precise on one axis, not on both.\n\nAnd I do agree with you @ellisonbg, in that the flashiness can be annoying.  For some reason yours flashes less than the blue bar in Sage, which I actually find a little distracting, so yours didn't bother me as much.  But still, I'm not crazy about visually flashing UI elements either.\n"
  },
