    "created_at": "2012-01-25T21:43:59Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-01-25T21:43:59Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "By the way, I just integrated jquery-touch-punch into our singlecell server, and it does a really nice job of mapping touch events to mouse events so that all the jquery ui controls just work with touch interfaces.  See http://furf.com/exp/touch-punch/\n\nAnd another by the way: you guys are more than welcome to incorporate our (BSD-licensed! :) interact implementation from the singlecell server into ipython.  In fact, I think that would be a great place for it to live.  Basically, that gives you the `@interact` functionality from Sage.  Our implementation is in https://github.com/sagemath/sagecell/blob/master/interact_singlecell.py (backend python module) and https://github.com/sagemath/sagecell/blob/master/static/compute_server.js (frontend javascript to create sliders, buttons, etc., included in that file).\n"
  },
