    "body": "Jason,\n\nOn Wed, Jan 25, 2012 at 1:44 PM, Jason Grout\nreply@reply.github.com\nwrote:\n\n> By the way, I just integrated jquery-touch-punch into our singlecell server, and it does a really nice job of mapping touch events to mouse events so that all the jquery ui controls just work with touch interfaces.  See http://furf.com/exp/touch-punch/\n\nI will check this out as we do want to improve the mobile experience.\n\n> And another by the way: you guys are more than welcome to incorporate our (BSD-licensed! :) interact implementation from the singlecell server into ipython.  In fact, I think that would be a great place for it to live.  Basically, that gives you the `@interact` functionality from Sage.  Our implementation is in https://github.com/sagemath/sagecell/blob/master/interact_singlecell.py (backend python module) and https://github.com/sagemath/sagecell/blob/master/static/compute_server.js (frontend javascript to create sliders, buttons, etc., included in that file).\n\nThanks for pointing us to this.  The interact capability is something\nwe are definitely thinking about.  Because this version is BSD, we\ncould use it as a starting point and they could be really helpful.  We\nwill keep this in mind and have a look at it.  Thanks!\n\n> ---\n> \n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub:\n> https://github.com/ipython/ipython/pull/1314#issuecomment-3659715\n\n## \n\nBrian E. Granger\nCal Poly State University, San Luis Obispo\nbgranger@calpoly.edu and ellisonbg@gmail.com\n"
