    "created_at": "2012-01-26T06:23:36Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-01-26T06:23:36Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Just to record my current take on this here (Brian and I had a skype chat): I vote for not doing this now, and wait until we can add UI control at the per-cell level done correctly.  Since we want to expose things like cell metadata, eventually we know we're going to have to figure out a solution to small UI controls per-cell, perhaps with a menu raised by the prompt area.  That would be a spatially local menu (being spatially close to the action is one advantage of the current PR that I acknowledge) while not having any cost in terms of vertical space or UI flashing visually.\n\nSo that's my vote; wait for now (there's still the menus and keybindings, so there are ways of getting new cells) and implement a clean solution later rather than hack in something that flashes and costs vertical space.\n"
  },
